<LegalLayout title="Privacy Policy">
  <p>
    Magna Cerámica respects your privacy and is committed to protecting your
    personal data in accordance with the EU General Data Protection Regulation
    (GDPR) and applicable Spanish data protection law.
  </p>

  <h2>1. Data controller</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Controller:</strong> Magna Cerámica SL (CIF B12466280)</li>
    <li><strong>Registered office:</strong> Avda. Casalduch 55, 12005 Castellón, Spain</li>
    <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:info@magnaceramica.es">info@magnaceramica.es</a></li>
    <li><strong>Phone:</strong> <a href="tel:+34964252250">+34 964 252 250</a></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>2. What data we collect</h2>
  <p>
    We only collect the data you voluntarily provide when you contact us — for
    example, through our contact form or by email: name, email address, phone
    number, and the content of your message. We also collect technical data
    through cookies, as described in our
    <a href="/cookies-policy">Cookies Policy</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>3. Purpose and legal basis</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>To respond to your enquiries</strong> and provide the information
      requested — legal basis: your consent and pre-contractual measures.</li>
    <li><strong>To manage commercial relationships</strong> with clients and
      partners — legal basis: legitimate interest and/or performance of a
      contract.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>We do not use your data for automated decision-making or profiling.</p>

  <h2>4. Data retention</h2>
  <p>
    We keep your data only for as long as necessary to fulfil the purpose for
    which it was collected and to comply with legal obligations, after which it
    is securely deleted.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Data sharing</h2>
  <p>
    We do not sell your personal data. Data may be shared with service providers
    that help us operate the Website under appropriate data processing
    agreements, including analytics (Google Analytics), mapping services (Google
    Maps), and email/communication tools (such as Mailchimp). These providers
    may process data outside the EU under the safeguards required by the GDPR.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Your rights</h2>
  <p>
    You have the right to access, rectify, erase, restrict, and object to the
    processing of your data, as well as the right to data portability. To
    exercise these rights, contact us at
    <a href="mailto:info@magnaceramica.es">info@magnaceramica.es</a>. You also
    have the right to lodge a complaint with the Spanish Data Protection Agency
    (AEPD, <a href="https://www.aepd.es">www.aepd.es</a>).
  </p>

  <h2>7. Security</h2>
  <p>
    We apply appropriate technical and organisational measures to protect your
    personal data against unauthorised access, alteration, or loss.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be
    published on this page with an updated revision date.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
